                            <comment id="161048" author="jamesanunez" created="Sat, 6 Aug 2016 23:23:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;From the test results the patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/16941&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/16941&lt;/a&gt; looks like sanity-sec is running in about two minutes; &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/e98c1392-275c-11e6-a8f9-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/e98c1392-275c-11e6-a8f9-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;. We should submit a patch to remove this test from the SLOW list. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="151902" author="kit.westneat" created="Wed, 11 May 2016 18:43:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That is correct. I can break the test_26 fix into a separate patch if it makes your lives easier. Or perhaps it can be added to the SKIP list until patch 16941 lands? What is the best way to proceed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="151034" author="jamesanunez" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 19:23:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this test is modified by patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/16941/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/16941/&lt;/a&gt; and passes testing; two cases passing in DNE setup at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/191fc420-fb87-11e5-acc0-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/191fc420-fb87-11e5-acc0-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/db3442d2-0598-11e6-b5f1-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/db3442d2-0598-11e6-b5f1-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, this problem may be cleaned up when patch 16941 lands.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
